140 THE ODES OF HORACE.

ODE V.

TO GABINIUS.

This poem is designated variously in the MSS. as “Lalage,'' “To the Lover of Lalage,” &c According to one early MS. (the Zurich), it is inscribed to· Gabinius. But even Estre cannot tell us who Gabinius was, though Orelli conjectures him to have been son or grandson to A. Gabinius, Cicero’s enemy. The poem is of very general application, and the leading idea is expressed with great elegance and spirit.
